cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.CY, cs.HC

The paper proposes a course recommender system for MOOCs that uses personalized context information and historical statistics to recommend courses. This involves handling dynamic and infinitely massive datasets, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and big data (cs.DB). The use of context information also suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the mention of storage modules and distributed-connected storage nodes suggests a focus on cybernetics (cs.CY).
